bool cds::map::split_list::details::split_list_base< KEY, VALUE, PAIR_TRAITS, TRAITS, ALLOCATOR >::emplace ( const KEY &  key,
const T &  val,
FUNC  func 
) [inline]

Emplaces the vale of key key with new value val.

The operation changes the value (or a part of the value) of key key to new one val. The user-defined functor func has the purpose like func argument of ensure member function. The signature of func is 

                        void func( VALUE& itemValue, const T& val ) ;

The first argument itemValue of user-defined function func is the reference to the list's item pointed by key key. The second argument val is the value passed to emplace member function. User-defined function func must guarantee that during changing key's value no any other changes could be made on this list's item by concurrent threads. The list only garantees that the item found by key cannot be deleted while func worked

The function returns true if the key key exists in the list.

template<typename KEY , typename VALUE , typename PAIR_TRAITS = pair_traits< KEY, VALUE >, typename TRAITS = split_list::type_traits, class ALLOCATOR = CDS_DEFAULT_ALLOCATOR>
template<typename FUNC >
std::pair<bool, bool> cds::map::split_list::details::split_list_base< KEY, VALUE, PAIR_TRAITS, TRAITS, ALLOCATOR >::ensure ( const KEY &  key,
const VALUE &  val,
FUNC  func 
) [inline]

Ensures that key key exists in the list.

If key exists in the list then changes the value of the item pointed by key to val. The change is performed by calling user-defined function func with signature: 

                            void func( VALUE& itemValue, const VALUE& val ) ;

The first argument itemValue of user-defined function func is the reference to the list's item pointed by key key. The second argument val is the value passed to ensure member function. User-defined function func must guarantee that during changing key's value no any other changes could be made on this list's item by concurrent threads. The user-defined function is called only if the key exists in the list.

If key is not in list then add it.

Returns std::pair<bool, bool> where first is true if operation is successfull, second is true if new item has been added or false if the item with key already in list.
